<item>
            <title>[LU-1379] kernel BUG at crypto/api.c:336!</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1379</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I just tested on lustre-2.2 with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1201&quot; title=&quot;Lustre crypto hash cleanup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1201&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1201&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patches. &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,2276&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,2276&lt;/a&gt; (patch set6) on Dell R620 which is Intel Sandybridge server. Once MDS mounts the mdt on MDS, it got the kernel panic. (kernel BUG at crypto/api.c:336!)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is new instalaltion testing, no upgrade from previous version. crc32c_intel is loaded, but loaded or not loaded don&apos;t matter. Tested on both cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Dell R620, RHEL6.2, lustre-2.2.0/w &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1201&quot; title=&quot;Lustre crypto hash cleanup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1201&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;LU-1201&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch </environment>
